{"body": "<p>The += marks cannot be used in VB.net you must use the AddHandler command.\nit is not the same syntax.</p>\n\n<pre><code>AddHandler MeasureItem, AddressOf OnMeasureItem\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Read this <a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/6yyk8z93(v=vs.90).aspx\" rel=\"nofollow\">Topic 1</a> <a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms743596.aspx?cs-save-lang=1&amp;cs-lang=vb#code-snippet-2\" rel=\"nofollow\">Topic 2</a>\nit may help you</p>\n\n<p>The same Issue is found <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/19354696/converting-c-sharp-eventhandler-code-to-vb-net\">Here</a></p>\n", "tags": ["vb.net"], "creation_date": 1477227408, "score": 0, "last_activity_date": 1477227408, "answer_id": 40203168, "is_accepted": false, "owner": {"user_id": 7031230, "reputation": 571, "user_type": "registered", "display_name": "H.Fadlallah", "link": "http://stackoverflow.com/users/7031230/h-fadlallah", "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a4dc60c72f95a8ea1106cdd4440234e9?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1"}, "title": "porting C# code to vb.net -- eventhandler", "question_id": 40202952}